f%20countries%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-leads-group-of-nations-that-buy-cheap-russian-oil-sell-processed-products-to-europe-report%5C%22%3Ehelps%20sidestep%20the%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20buying%20discounted%20Russian%20crude%20oil%2C%20refining%20it%20and%20selling%20the%20processed%20products%20to%20European%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20global%20oil%20prices%20have%20been%20on%20the%20decline%20and%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20crude%20oil%20variety%20is%20priced%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Findias-russian-oil-imports-seen-rising-lower-prices-official-2023-12-08%2F%5C%22%3Eless%20than%20%2460%20per%20barrel%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20ports%20at%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20help%20India%20import%20greater%20quantities%20of%20Russian%20crude%20oil%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702465258000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F28110029%2F11147221423_303ec1a1d8_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findia-paid-84-20-per-barrel-russian-crude-oil-highest-since-west-sanctions-last-year%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russian%20oil%20reportedly%20made%20up%2040%25%20of%20Indian%20imports%20of%20the%20product%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20fiscal%20year%202023-2024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findia-paid-84-20-per-barrel-russian-crude-oil-highest-since-west-sanctions-last-year%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Assault%20Rifle%20Induction%20Woes%20Continue%20With%20Delays%20in%20Indigenous%20Ak-203%20Production%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13154542%2F050626c14821e821a98ed6661b4555d2.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Indian%20military%E2%80%99s%20acute%20labour%20pains%20for%20nearly%2013%20years%20with%20regard%20to%20inducting%20assault%20rifles%20endure%2C%20with%20the%20latest%20obstacle%20being%20the%20delay%20in%20the%20indigenous%20production%20of%20Russian%20Kalashnikov%20Ak-203%20assault%20rifles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20postponement%20by%20the%20Indo-Russian%20Rifles%20Private%20Limited%20(IRRPL)%20joint%20venture%20(JV)%20at%20Korwa%2C%20near%20Amethi%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20following%20US-led%20sanctions%20on%20Moscow%20for%20invading%20Ukraine%2C%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20compelled%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD)%20to%20recently%20approve%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20(IA%E2%80%99s)%20request%20for%20the%20follow-on%20import%20of%2073%2C000%20%E2%80%98Patrol%E2%80%99%20Sig%20assault%20rifles%20from%20the%20US%20for%20Rs%20840%20crore%2C%20to%20meet%20urgent%20operational%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20in%20late%202020%2C%20the%20MoD%20had%20procured%2072%2C400%20SIG716%20Sauer%207.62x51mm%20rifles%20for%20around%20Rs%20700%20crore%2C%20of%20which%20the%20IA%20had%20received%2066%2C400%20units%2C%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%204%2C000%20and%20the%20Indian%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20Garud%20Special%20Forces%20the%20remaining%202%2C000%20weapon%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20soon%20after%20the%20rifle%20buy%2C%20the%20MoD%20had%20proscribed%20all%20assault%20rifle%20imports%20and%20included%20the%20weapon%20system%20in%20its%20Positive%20Indigenisation%20List.%20Five%20such%20lists%20comprised%20509%20military%20platforms%20and%20related%20items%20and%20equipment%20that%20were%20to%20be%20sourced%20locally%20within%20a%20staggered%20schedule%20lasting%20till%202025.%20According%20to%20this%20time%20table%2C%20however%2C%20the%20purchase%20of%20foreign%20assault%20rifles%20was%20to%20have%20mandatorily%20ceased%20by%20December%202021%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20overall%20bid%20to%20further%20the%20MoD%E2%80%99s%20atmanirbhar%20or%20self-sufficiency%20initiative%20with%20regard%20to%20locally%20sourcing%20military%20kit%20and%20reducing%20import%20dependency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndustry%20officials%20said%20that%20by%20approving%20the%2073%2C000%20Sig%20Sauer%20rifle%20import%2C%20the%20MoD%E2%80%99s%20Defence%20Acquisition%20Council%20was%20%E2%80%98contravening%E2%80%99%20its%20own%20stipulations.%20They%20also%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%98indirectly%E2%80%99%20acknowledging%20that%20the%20IRRPL%20at%20Korwa%2C%20which%20was%20inaugurated%20in%20early%202019%20and%20slated%20to%20begin%20supplying%20Ak-203%20rifles%20to%20the%20IA%20by%20March%202024%2C%20had%20failed%20to%20meet%20its%20delivery%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20the%20IA%20Chief%20of%20Staff%20General%20Manoj%20Pande%20had%20declared%20that%20army%20would%20receive%20its%20first%20batch%20of%205%2C000%20locally%20manufactured%20Ak-203%207.62x39mm%20rifles%20but%2C%20for%20now%2C%20these%20stood%20jeopardised%2C%20reportedly%20necessitating%20the%20proposed%20Sig%20Sauer%20rifle%20import.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIA%20officials%20and%20those%20at%20the%20IRRPL%20in%20Korwa%20were%20unavailable%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20news%20reports%20also%20dismissed%20accounts%20of%20glitches%20in%20the%20previous%20SIG716%20rifles%20consignment%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fwith-snags-reported-defence-ministry-decides-against-repeating-us-assault-rifle-order%5C%22%3Ewhich%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20in%20May%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20industry%20officials%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20report%20had%20said%20that%20these%20snags%20centred%20on%20some%20rifles%20%E2%80%98jamming%E2%80%99%20whilst%20firing%20locally%20produced%207.62mm%20rounds%2C%20which%20were%20not%20as%20efficient%20as%20imported%20ammunition.%20Hence%2C%20when%20fired%20they%20reportedly%20tended%2C%20in%20many%20instances%2C%20to%20spawn%20%E2%80%98barrel%20bulges%E2%80%99%20that%20rendered%20many%20rifle%E2%80%99s%20inoperable.%20These%20bulges%20ensued%20after%20a%20round%20failed%20to%20exit%20the%20rifle%20upon%20firing%20and%20the%20follow-on%20round%20built%20up%20tremendous%20pressure%20due%20to%20the%20constricted%20air%20inside%20the%20barrel%2C%20causing%20it%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20to%20either%20develop%20a%20bulge%2C%20a%20crack%20or%20even%20result%20in%20it%20exploding%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArmy%20sources%20had%20also%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20the%20time%20that%20indigenous%20ammunition%20also%20rendered%20%E2%80%98somewhat%20questionable%20and%20inaccurate%E2%80%99%20the%20rifles%20second%20round%20burst%20accuracy.%20In%20a%20semi-automatic%20firearm%20like%20the%20SIG716%2C%20%E2%80%98burst-mode%E2%80%99%20firing%20enabled%20the%20shooter%20to%20fire%20a%20predetermined%20number%20of%20rounds-normally%20two%20or%20three-%20at%20a%20target%20with%20a%20single%20pull%20of%20the%20trigger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20these%20SIG76%20rifles%20had%20reportedly%20necessitated%20local%20%E2%80%98modifications%E2%80%99%20like%20altering%20their%20grip%20to%20enable%20a%20firmer%20grasp%20by%20adding%20a%20%E2%80%98wooden%20handle%E2%80%99%20under%20their%20457.2mm%20long%20barrel%2C%20somewhat%20similar%20to%20the%20jugaad%20or%20innovation%20the%20IA%20had%20earlier%20executed%20on%20Ak-47%E2%80%99s.%20Recent%20media%20reports%20also%20claimed%20that%20some%20army%20units%20had%20locally%20fitted%20the%20SIG716%E2%80%99s%20with%20these%20%E2%80%98grips%E2%80%99%20as%20well%20as%20with%20bipods%20to%20provide%20the%20rifles%20stability%20against%20canting%2C%20or%20side-to-side%20movement%2C%20thereby%20augmenting%20their%20operational%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20above%20all%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20stated%20that%20the%20SIG716%20rifles%20lacked%20optical%20day%2C%20night%2C%20holographic%20and%20even%20basic%20LED-powered%20reflex%20%E2%80%98red-dot%E2%80%99%20sights%20as%20the%20MoD%2C%20under%20IA%20advisement%20had%2C%20out%20of%20pecuniary%20considerations%2C%20decided%20against%20acquiring%20these%20critical%20auxiliary%20add-ons%2C%20essential%20to%20precisely%20aligning%20targets%20in%20conflict%20zones%20at%20ranges%20varying%20between%20100m-700m.%20The%20latter%20battery-operated%20sight%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20provided%20users%20a%20%E2%80%98point%20of%20aim%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20form%20of%20an%20illuminated%20red%20dot%2C%20a%20phenomenon%20often%20seen%20in%20action%20movies%3B%20their%20absence%20renders%20the%20user%20wholly%20or%20at%20least%20partially%20%E2%80%98blind%E2%80%99%20in%20skirmish%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20not%20having%20any%20of%20these%20sights%20to%20secure%20a%20virtual%20image%20of%20the%20intended%20mark%20required%20the%20shooter%20to%20close%20one%20eye%20to%20make%20his%20objective%2C%20thus%20depriving%20him%20of%20peripheral%20vision%2C%20that%20could%20well%20determine%20the%20stark%20choice%20between%20life%20and%20death%20on%20the%20battlefield.%20Conversely%2C%20the%20day%20and%20night%20sights%2C%20depending%20on%20their%20respective%20magnifications%20and%20sophistication%20were%20more%20advanced%2C%20but%20expensive%20to%20import%2C%20costing%20upwards%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%20each%2C%20for%20which%20reason%20the%20MoD%20had%20obviated%20their%20procurement.%20It%20had%20then%20reasoned%20that%20indigenous%20substitutes%20were%20cheaper..%20Thereafter%2C%20several%20local%20manufacturers%20had%20demonstrated%20assorted%20sights%20at%20the%20Army%20War%20College%20at%20Mhow%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20for%20eventual%20fitment%20onto%20the%20SIG716%E2%80%99s%2C%20some%20of%20which%20were%20under%20evaluation%20and%20awaited%20shortlisting%20to%20render%20the%20rifles%20operationally%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20the%20IA%20was%20effectively%20employing%20domestically%20sourced%207.62mm%20rounds%2C%20and%20quoted%20an%20unidentified%20army%20officer%20declaring%20that%20as%20a%20consequence%20%E2%80%9Cno%20deviations%20in%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20weapon%20had%20been%20found%E2%80%9D.%20Its%20report%20also%20quoted%20the%20same%20officer%20claiming%20that%20the%20SIG716%20rifle%20had%20a%20500m%20%E2%80%98kill%20range%E2%80%99%20compared%20to%20the%20Ak-203%E2%80%99s%20300m%2C%20thereby%20justifying%20the%20purchase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20officer%20also%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20rifles%20were%20fitted%20with%20Picatinny%20rails%20to%20facilitate%20the%20mounting%20of%20various%20equipment%20and%20accessories%2C%20such%20as%20optical%20sights%2C%20under%20barrel%20grenade%20launchers%2C%20bipods%20and%20laser%20pointers%20and%20other%20force%20multipliers%20without%20modifications.%20But%20he%20declined%20to%20confirm%20if%20any%20or%20all%20these%20additional%20fixtures%20had%20either%20previously%20been%20procured%20or%20were%20in%20the%20future%20being%20acquired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ak-203%20saga%20began%20after%20the%20IA%E2%80%99s%20wholly%20impractical%20multi-calibre%20assault%20rifle%20tender%20was%20eventually%20terminated%20in%202015%20after%20five%20fruitless%20years%20of%20trials%20and%20evaluations%20following%20a%20flawed%20qualitative%20requirement%20(QR)%20formulated%20by%20the%20Infantry%20Directorate%20for%20the%20weapon%20system.%20The%20proposed%20rifles%20were%20intended%20to%20replace%20the%20indigenously%20developed%20Indian%20Small%20Arms%20System%20(INSAS)%205.56x45mm%20assault%20rifles%20that%20had%20entered%20IA%20service%20in%20the%20mid-1990%E2%80%99s%2C%20but%20were%20seriously%20flawed%20and%20ultimately%20declared%20%E2%80%98operationally%E2%80%99%20inadequate%20by%20the%20force%20in%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20disastrous%20multi-calibre%20procurement%20was%20rescinded%20the%20IA%2C%20yet%20again%20amazingly%20re-ignited%20deliberations%20over%20which%20calibre%20rifle%20%E2%80%93%205.56mm%20or%207.62mm%20%E2%80%93%20it%20operationally%20required%2C%20before%20opting%20for%20the%20former%20after%20years%20of%20tortuous%20wranglings.%20Its%20attempts%20to%20source%20an%20assault%20rifle%20from%20the%20erstwhile%20state-run%20Ordnance%20Factory%20Board%20(OFB)%20also%20failed.%20But%20four%20years%20later%2C%20in%20March%202019%2C%20just%20ahead%20of%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20inaugurated%20the%20facility%20at%20Korwa%20to%20licence%20build%20750%2C000%20Ak-203%20rifles%20with%20collapsible%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20JV%20to%20implement%20the%20project%20followed%20an%20Inter-Governmental%20Agreement%20(IGA)%20between%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Moscow%20that%20was%20signed%20soon%20after%20in%20which%20the%20OFB%20had%20a%2050.5%25%20stake%20in%20IRPL%2C%20the%20Kalashnikov%20Group%2042%25%20and%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20state-owned%20arms%20export%20agency%20Rosonboronexport%2C%20the%20remaining%207.5%25.%20The%20OFBs%20Korwa%20project%20has%20since%20been%20assimilated%20into%20the%20newly%20formed%20Advanced%20Weapon%20and%20Equipment%20India%20Limited%20corporation%20after%20OFB%20was%20split%20into%20seven%20assorted%20government-owned%20entities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intent%20was%20for%20IRRPL%20to%20import%20some%2080%2C0000%20AK-203%E2%80%99s%20for%20around%20%241%2C100%20(Rs%2081%2C000)%20apiece%20to%20meet%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20urgent%20operational%20needs%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20licensed%20production%20of%20the%20remaining%20650%2C000-odd%20units.%20But%20the%20deal%20ran%20into%20multitudinous%20problems%20of%20costing%2C%20payment%20of%20royalties%20and%20technology%20transfer%20issues%20like%20the%20indigenous%20content%20to%20be%20incorporated%20into%20the%20rifles.%20Sundry%20contractual%20and%20pricing%20problems%20too%20persisted%2C%20with%20the%20former%20OFB%20having%20costed%20each%20licence-built%20Ak-203%20rifle%20initially%20at%20around%20Rs%2086%2C000.%20Amortised%20over%20time%20its%20cost%20was%20projected%20to%20drop%20to%20around%20Rs%2080%2C000%20per%20unit%2C%20still%20more%20than%20each%20Sig%20Sauer%20rifle%20which%20at%20the%20time%20was%20considerably%20cheaper%20at%20Rs%2072%2C782.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20related%20development%2C%20industry%20officials%20claimed%20that%20the%20IA%20was%20currently%20considering%20%E2%80%98upgrading%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98re-tweaking%E2%80%99%20its%20INSAS%20assault%20rifle%20which%20it%20had%20discarded%20over%20a%20decade%20ago%20on%20grounds%20of%20inefficiency%20and%20for%20being%20a%20weapon%20system%20%E2%80%98overtaken%20by%20technological%20development%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20a%20euphemism%20for%20the%20rifle%20imply%20being%20a%20poorly%20designed%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shortcomings%20of%20the%20domestic%20rifle%2C%20developed%20over%20a%20decade%20by%20the%20Defence%20Research%20and%20Development%20Organisation%20and%20series%20built%20thereafter%20by%20the%20former%20OFB%2C%20centred%20round%20its%20sights%2C%20which%20malfunctioned%20especially%20in%20extreme%20temperatures%E2%80%99%20and%20its%20firing%20mechanism%20that%20often%20jammed%20during%20firefights.%20But%20successive%20army%20chiefs%2C%20presented%20a%20fait%20accompli%2C%20had%20un-demurringly%20persisted%20in%20employing%20the%20INSAS%20rifle%20that%20was%20the%20infantry%E2%80%99s%20principal%20weapon%20during%20the%20Kargil%20war%20and%20in%20counter-insurgency%20operations%2C%20much%20to%20the%20operational%20chagrin%20of%20numerous%20combat%20formations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIA%20plans%20to%20retrofit%20and%20modify%20the%20INSAS%20rifle%20are%20believed%20to%20include%20refashioning%20its%20butt%20stock%20to%20ensure%20sustained%20fire%20under%20adverse%20conditions%2C%20minimising%20its%20high%20recoil%2C%20and%20installing%20%E2%80%98lower%E2%80%99%20Picatinny%20rails%20to%20support%20accessories%20and%20add-ons%2C%20amongst%20other%20modifications.%20A%20private%20vendor%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20successfully%20upgraded%20the%20INSAS%20for%20employment%20for%20some%20paramilitary%20and%20state%20police%20units%2C%20and%20has%20reportedly%20offered%20the%20same%20to%20the%20IA%20which%20was%20favourably%20considering%20his%20proposal%20to%20make%20good%20its%20needs%20for%20its%20basic%20infantry%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20a%20senior%20veteran%20infantry%20officer%20quipped%2C%20such%20a%20move%20would%20merely%20entail%20throwing%20good%20money%20after%20bad.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20responsibility%20for%20these%20continuing%20setbacks%20lies%20equally%20with%20the%20services%20for%20their%20flawed%20planning%20and%20the%20MoD%20for%20its%20rigid%20and%20byzantine%20procedures%20that%20few%20can%20comprehend%20and%20even%20fewer%20implement%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20former%20defence%20ministry%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20following%20a%20practical%20and%20realistic%20approach%20to%20military%20capability%20development%2C%20the%20services%20and%20the%20MoD%20are%20forever%20engaged%20in%20a%20tussle%20that%20obviates%20its%20attainment%20he%20added%2C%20declining%20to%20be%20identified%20as%20he%20was%20fearful%20of%20repercussions%2C%20despite%20having%20retired.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702464351000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13154542%2F050626c14821e821a98ed6661b4555d2.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Findias-assault-rifle-induction-woes-continue-with-delays-in-indigenous-ak-203-production%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Because%20of%20this%20delay%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20has%20approved%20the%20Indian%20Army's%20request%20for%20the%20follow-on%20import%20of%2073%2C000%20%E2%80%98Patrol%E2%80%99%20Sig%20assault%20ri