ngagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frussian-stowaway-feasted-on-plane-food-after-boarding-copenhagen-to-la-flight-without-ticket-or-passport-fbi-says-13029373%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Frussian-stowaway-feasted-on-plane-food-after-boarding-copenhagen-to-la-flight-without-ticket-or-passport-fbi-says-13029373%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Frussian-stowaway-feasted-on-plane-food-after-boarding-copenhagen-to-la-flight-without-ticket-or-passport-fbi-says-13029373%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Governors'%20Pocket%20Veto%20Compromises%20Constitutional%20Probity%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F27102504%2FKolkata%25E2%2580%2599s-Raj-Bhavan-could-be-worth-almost-Rs-2000-crores-today-FB-1200x700-compressed.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Fbjp-disinfo-machine-milking-gaza%5C%22%3Epiece%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20published%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20India%20Cable%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%C2%A0a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%C2%A0The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ERecent%20observation%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20the%20increasing%20tendency%20of%20some%20governors%20to%20hold%20indefinitely%20the%20Bills%20passed%20by%20state%20Assemblies%20has%20far-reaching%20consequences%20in%20strengthening%20the%20federal%20polity%20of%20India.%20If%20this%20had%20happened%20in%20one%20state%2C%20it%20could%20be%20read%20as%20the%20eccentricity%20of%20a%20particular%20individual%20in%20a%20position%20of%20authority.%20When%20a%20similar%20lack%20of%20probity%20is%20seen%20amongst%20the%20constitutional%20heads%20of%20many%20states%20run%20by%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20that%20indicates%20design%20and%20raises%20the%20alarm.%20The%20apex%20court%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpower%20to%20take%20decisions%20affecting%20the%20governance%20of%20the%20state%20or%20the%20nation%20is%20essentially%20entrusted%20to%20the%20elected%20arm%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%9D.%20The%20increasing%20tendency%20of%20governors%20to%20act%20on%20their%20own%2C%20ignoring%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%20is%20like%20%E2%80%9Cplaying%20with%20fire%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20present%20impasse%20in%20many%20Opposition-run%20states%20reminds%20us%20of%20a%20similar%20incident%20at%20the%20national%20level%20almost%20four%20decades%20ago%2C%20when%20the%20relationship%20between%20prime%20minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20and%20president%20Giani%20Zail%20Singh%20had%20reached%20a%20nadir%20and%20that%20almost%20created%20a%20constitutional%20deadlock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EArticle%2074(1)%20of%20the%20constitution%20states%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccouncil%20of%20ministers%20headed%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20shall%20aid%20and%20advise%20the%20president%20in%20the%20exercise%20of%20his%20duties%E2%80%9D.%20Is%20that%20advice%20binding%20on%20the%20president%3F%20The%2042nd%20Amendment%20(1976)%20of%20the%20constitution%20made%20the%20advice%20binding.%20However%2C%20the%2044th%20Amendment%20(1978)%20stated%20that%20the%20president%20can%20send%20the%20advice%20back%20to%20the%20council%20for%20reconsideration%20for%20once.%20If%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%20sends%20the%20same%20advice%20again%20to%20the%20president%2C%20he%20must%20accept%20it.%20Is%20there%20any%20time%20limit%20prescribed%20in%20the%20constitution%20for%20the%20president%20to%20accept%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%3F%20Unfortunately%2C%20that%20is%20not%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPresident%20Giani%20Zail%20Singh%20did%20not%20give%20his%20assent%20to%20the%20Indian%20Post%20Office%20(Amendment)%20Bill%20(1986)%20after%20the%20Bill%20was%20passed%20in%20Parliament.%20He%20sat%20on%20the%20Bill%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20tenure%2C%20which%20created%20a%20kind%20of%20constitutional%20impasse%20at%20that%20time.%20Was%20it%20ethical%20of%20the%20president%20to%20veto%20a%20Bill%20passed%20by%20Parliament%3F%20Such%20an%20impasse%20did%20not%20recur%2C%20not%20even%20when%20the%20incumbent%20presidents%20were%20from%20a%20political%20party%20opposed%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20at%20the%20Centre%20%E2%80%95%20K.R.%20Narayanan%20during%20NDA-1%20or%20Pranab%20Mukherjee%20during%20NDA-2%20rule.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20supremacy%20of%20parliament%20in%20Indian%20democracy%20was%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-as-ruling-partys-storm-troopers%5C%22%3EGovernors%20as%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Storm%20Troopers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20present%20trend%20of%20a%20few%20governors%20keeping%20Bills%20passed%20by%20Assemblies%20pending%20indefinitely%20undermines%20the%20authority%20of%20elected%20governments.%20Under%20Article%20201%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20a%20Bill%20can%20be%20reserved%20by%20the%20governor%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20president%2C%20if%20the%20content%20of%20the%20Bill%20has%20national%20ramifications.%20The%20president%20may%20give%20his%20assent%2C%20may%20withhold%20or%20even%20send%20back%20a%20Bill%20to%20the%20governor%2C%20with%20the%20direction%20to%20return%20it%20to%20the%20state%20Assembly%20for%20reconsideration.%20However%2C%20if%20the%20governor%20has%20not%20reserved%20the%20Bill%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20president%2C%20he%20has%20to%20act%20as%20per%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EArticle%20200%20of%20the%20Constitution%20clearly%20states%20that%20once%20a%20Bill%20is%20passed%20in%20the%20state%20Assembly%20and%20presented%20to%20the%20governor%2C%20he%20or%20she%20must%20either%20approve%20the%20Bill%20or%20return%20it%20with%20a%20request%20to%20the%20House%20to%20%E2%80%9Creconsider%20the%20Bill%20or%20any%20specified%20provisions%20thereof%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20to%20do%20so%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D.%20If%20the%20House%20passes%20the%20Bill%20after%20reconsideration%20with%20or%20without%20amendment%2C%20and%20the%20Bill%20is%20presented%20to%20the%20governor%20for%20the%20second%20time%2C%20he%20shall%20not%20withhold%20assent.%20Article%20200%20did%20not%20fix%20any%20timeline%20for%20the%20governor%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20matter.%20That%20loophole%20is%20being%20used%20by%20Raj%20Bhavans%20for%20deliberate%20procrastination.%20The%20apex%20court%20observed%20that%20governors%20cannot%20sit%20on%20Bills%20indefinitely%20without%20disclosing%20reasons%20for%20delay.%20Though%20the%20constitution%20provides%20complete%20immunity%20to%20governors%20from%20court%20proceedings%2C%20they%20cannot%20act%20arbitrarily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Sarkaria%20Commission%2C%20set%20up%20in%201983%20to%20examine%20Centre-state%20relations%2C%20had%20recommended%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20governor%20should%20be%20eminent%20in%20some%20walks%20of%20life%20and%20not%20too%20intimately%20connected%20with%20local%20politics%20of%20the%20state%2C%20and%20he%20should%20be%20a%20person%20who%20has%20not%20taken%20too%20great%20a%20part%20in%20politics%2C%20in%20general%2C%20and%20in%20the%20recent%20past%20in%20particular%E2%80%9D.%20Unfortunately%2C%20these%20guidelines%20were%20never%20taken%20seriously%20by%20subsequent%20Union%20governments.%20The%20Union%20government%20will%20hopefully%20be%20more%20judicious%20in%20the%20future%20about%20selecting%20governors%2C%20after%20what%20has%20been%20said%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Governors%20of%20the%20states%20also%20need%20to%20learn%20from%20the%20precedents%20created%20by%20presidents%20of%20the%20republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGautam%20Bhattacharya%20is%20a%20former%20university%20teacher%20and%20former%20additional%20secretary%20to%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702461630000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F27102504%2FKolkata%25E2%2580%2599s-Raj-Bhavan-could-be-worth-almost-Rs-2000-crores-today-FB-1200x700-compressed.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgovernors-pocket-veto-compromises-constitutional-probity%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20tendency%20of%20governors%20sitting%20indefinitely%20on%20Bills%20cleared%20by%20state%20Assemblies%20raises%20alarm.%20When%20a%20lack%20of%20probity%20is%20seen%20amongst%20the%20constitutional%20heads%20of%20many%20states%20run%20by%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20it%20indicates%20design.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgovernors-pocket-veto-compromises-constitutional-probity%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Spain%20records%20hottest%20December%20day%20as%20nation's%20ski%20season%20at%20risk%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702460160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-spain-heat_6391619.jpg%3F20231213101011%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fspain-records-hottest-december-day-as-nations-ski-season-at-risk-13029351%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mainland%20Spain%20has%20recorded%20its%20hottest%20December%20day%2C%20putting%20the%20nation's%20ski%20season%20at%20risk.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fspain-records-hottest-december-day-as-nations-ski-season-at-risk-13029351%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fspain-records-hottest-december-day-as-nations-ski-season-at-risk-13029351%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fspain-records-hottest-december-day-as-nations-ski-season-at-risk-13029351%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Will%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20Article%20370%20Judgment%20Mean%20for%20Politics%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13140041%2F16147040338_e14a11ca31_o.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20With%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20setting%20a%20deadline%20for%20assembly%20polls%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20speculations%20are%20rife%20on%20how%20the%20new%20constitutional%20architecture%20designed%20for%20the%20region%20by%20the%20BJP-led%20Union%20government%20will%20influence%20the%20first%20major%20electoral%20exercise%20post%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelivering%20a%20historic%20verdict%20on%20Monday%2C%20December%2011%2C%20a%20constitution%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20to%20conduct%20assembly%20polls%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20by%20September%2030%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20came%20as%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20set%20to%20complete%20five%20years%20under%20Central%20rule%20on%20December%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20repeatedly%20refused%20to%20conduct%20assembly%20elections%2C%20citing%20security%20issues%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20among%20other%20reasons%2C%20even%20as%20the%20poll%20body%20is%20preparing%20to%20hold%20the%20parliamentary%20elections%20in%20the%20union%20territory%20(UT).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20ECI%20will%20revive%20the%20democratic%20process%2C%20which%20has%20been%20put%20on%20a%20back%20burner%20since%202018%2C%20and%20allow%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20to%20exercise%20their%20democratic%20right%2C%20remains%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20speculation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20certain%20is%20that%20the%20saffron%20party%20would%20like%20to%20come%20to%20power%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20only%20Muslim-majority%20region%20on%20its%20own%2C%20ideally%20with%20a%20Hindu%20chief%20minister%2C%20after%20getting%20judicial%20approval%20for%20its%20%E2%80%98big%20move%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Noor%20A.%20Baba%2C%20former%20dean%20of%20social%20sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20believes%20that%20the%20BJP-led%20Union%20government%20has%20%E2%80%9Cpolitically%20engineered%E2%80%9D%20J%26amp%3BK%20after%20downgrading%20it%20into%20a%20union%20territory%20which%20could%20influence%20the%20outcome%20of%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019%20became%20a%20law%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20redrew%20the%20electoral%20landscape%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20When%20the%20controversial%20delimitation%20exercise%20was%20over%2C%20Jammu%2C%20a%20BJP%20stronghold%2C%20woke%20up%20with%20six%20additional%20assembly%20seats%20in%20its%20kitty%20while%20Kashmir%20got%20just%20one%20extra%20seat%2C%20despite%20a%20clear%20demographic%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDelimitation%20has%20completely%20changed%20the%20electoral%20arithmetic%20and%20tilted%20the%20balance%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20BJP.%20Even%20some%20electoral%20boundaries%20have%20been%20carved%20to%20ensure%20Hindu%20majority%20in%20some%20constituencies%20of%20Rajouri%2C%20Reasi%20and%20Chenab%20valley%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Jammu-based%20author%20and%20editor%20Anuradha%20Bhasin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Ends%20Matter%2C%20Not%20the%20Means%3A%20Decoding%20SC's%20Approval%20for%20Reading%20Down%20of%20Article%20370%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fends-matter-not-the-means-decoding-scs-approval-for-reading-down-of-article-370%5C%22%3EEnds%20Matter%2C%20Not%20the%20Means%3A%20Decoding%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Approval%20for%20Reading%20Down%20of%20Article%20370%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20saffron%20party%20is%20also%20reaching%20out%20to%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20Gujjars%2C%20Bakkerwals%20and%20Paharis%20by%20raising%20the%20bogey%20of%20%E2%80%98empowering%20the%20marginalised%E2%80%99%20with%20a%20new%20reservation%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20day%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20delivered%20its%20verdict%20on%20Article%20370%2C%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20gave%20its%20nod%20to%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reorganisation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%20which%20increases%20the%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Legislative%20Assembly%20from%2083%20to%2090%20of%20which%20seven%20seats%20are%20reserved%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%2C%20in%20a%20first%2C%20nine%20for%20Scheduled%20Tribes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20empowers%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20to%20nominate%20two%20members%20from%20the%20Kashmiri%20migrant%20community%20and%20one%20from%20Displaced%20Persons%20from%20Pakistan-occupied%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20to%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaba%20said%20that%20given%20India%E2%80%99s%20federal%20structure%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20should%20have%20left%20these%20landmark%20changes%20for%20a%20democratic%20dispensation%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20to%20undertake%2C%20asserting%20that%20in%20the%20process%20%E2%80%9CKashmir%20has%20been%20marginalised%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%20has%20been%20manoeuvred%20in%20a%20manner%20which%20has%20reduced%20the%20majority%20into%20a%20minority%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20changes%20effected%20by%20the%20delimitation%20and%20assembly%20reservation%20might%20help%20the%20BJP%20to%20cross%20the%20mark%20of%2025%20seats%20it%20had%20won%20in%202014%20assembly%20elections%2C%20even%20its%20most%20fervent%20supporters%20know%20that%20the%20party%20can%E2%80%99t%20come%20close%20to%20magic%20number%20of%2046%20required%20to%20form%20the%20government%20in%20the%20new%2C%2090-member%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20effect%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20been%20mollycoddling%20with%20like-minded%20leaders%20and%20Kashmir-centric%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202019%2C%20two%20new%20formations%20have%20also%20sprouted%20on%20the%20political%20horizon%20which%20are%20led%20by%20former%20J%26amp%3BK%20chief%20minister%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%20and%20former%20leader%20of%20Mehbooba%20Mufti%E2%80%99s%20PDP%2C%20Altaf%20Bukhari%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20have%20made%20public%20displays%20of%20affection%20for%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20National%20Conference%20(NC)%20and%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%2C%20who%20are%20part%20of%20the%20fledgling%20Gupkar%20alliance%2C%20have%20vowed%20to%20fight%20the%20BJP%20and%20restore%20Article%20370.%20But%20the%20two%20are%20also%20facing%20perhaps%20the%20most%20difficult%20times%20in%20their%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Rekha%20Chaudhary%2C%20a%20Jammu-based%20academic%20and%20political%20analyst%2C%20believes%20that%20the%20next%20assembly%20election%20will%20be%20a%20direct%20contest%20between%20the%20BJP%20and%20National%20Conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Kashmir%2C%20it%20is%20the%20NC%20which%20is%20quite%20confident%20of%20doing%20well.%20Not%20only%20because%20it%20showed%20its%20strength%20during%20the%20DDC%20elections%20held%20couple%20of%20years%20earlier%20but%20also%20because%20the%20PDP%20has%20been%20crisis-ridden%20with%20senior%20leaders%20leaving%20it%20over%20the%20period.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9COther%20parties%2C%20including%20Sajad%20Lone%E2%80%99s%20Peoples%20Conference%2C%20have%20a%20limited%20influence%20and%20they%20may%20well%20end%20up%20on%20the%20other%20side%20after%20the%20elections%20results%20are%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20political%20analyst%20and%20editor%20Zafar%20Choudhary%20believes%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20has%20brought%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfundamental%20change%E2%80%9D%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20political%20environment%20and%20the%20situation%20might%20%E2%80%9Cget%20difficult%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20local%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Kashmir%2C%20BJP%20has%20allies%20in%20a%20political%20environment%20where%20no%20party%20can%20get%20any%20serious%20listeners%20to%20the%20claims%20of%20being%20pro-special%20status.%20This%20%E2%80%98level%20playing%20field%E2%80%99%20opens%20space%20for%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20local%20allies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Choudhary%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Gupkar%20alliance%20getting%20sucked%20into%20petty%20political%20tirades%2C%20political%20analysts%20believe%20J%26amp%3BK%20assembly%20elections%20could%20well%20turn%20into%20an%20exercise%20in%20vanity%20with%20a%20pie%20of%20power%20hanging%20for%20anyone%20willing%20to%20share%20the%20spoils.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Jammu%2C%20which%20helped%20the%20BJP%20more%20than%20double%20its%20tally%20in%20the%202014%20assembly%20election%2C%20might%20not%20be%20a%20cakewalk%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20Jammu%20region%2C%20though%20the%20BJP%20is%20facing%20multiple%20challenges%2C%20it%20is%20also%20comfortable%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20is%20no%20alternative%20to%20it.%20The%20Congress%2C%20the%20only%20party%20that%20could%20have%20challenged%20it%2C%20has%20been%20weakened%20after%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20exit%20and%20his%20party%20has%20not%20really%20taken%20off.%20NC%20has%20almost%20withdrawn%20from%20the%20region%20and%20is%20mainly%20focusing%20on%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chaudhary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20exit%20of%20Devendra%20Rana%20and%20S.S.%20Slathia%2C%20the%20NC%E2%80%99s%20most%20visible%20Jammu%20faces%20who%20have%20since%20switched%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20party%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20be%20active%20in%20the%20plains%20of%20Jammu.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20this%20leaves%20the%20field%20open%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chaudhary%2C%20who%20taught%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Jammu%2C%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Kashmir%2C%20analysts%20believe%20that%20the%20election%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20no-holds-barred%20contest%20where%20the%20traditional%20parties%20like%20NC%20and%20PDP%20will%20struggle%20and%20bleed%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20multi-pronged%20assault%20which%20has%20sent%20dozens%20of%20their%20leaders%20flocking%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98right%E2%80%99%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20the%20exception%20of%20the%20PDP%20which%20has%20not%20changed%20much%20of%20its%20basic%20orientation%2C%20other%20parties%20have%20almost%20moved%20on.%20The%20NC%2C%20mainly%20because%20of%20the%20future%20that%20it%20sees%20for%20itself%20in%20the%20coming%20elections%2C%20has%20adopted%20a%20more%20pragmatic%20approach.%20Much%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%2C%20it%20had%20delinked%20its%20politics%20from%20the%20issue%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20stating%20that%20this%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98legal%20issue%E2%80%99%20pending%20with%20the%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalyst%20Choudhary%20said%20that%20any%20party%20or%20alliance%20will%20have%20to%20win%2048%20seats%2C%20three%20more%20than%20the%20halfway%20mark%20of%2045%20seats%2C%20to%20form%20the%20next%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20allies%20will%20need%20only%2043%20seats%20as%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20is%20empowered%20to%20nominate%20three%20members.%20Given%20the%20voting%20pattern%20of%20the%20last%20three%20assembly%20elections%2C%20it%20is%20unlikely%20for%20any%20alliance%20to%20clinch%20the%20magic%20number%20of%2048%2C%E2%80%9D%20Choudhary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20case%20of%20a%20close%20contest%2C%20three%20officially%20nominated%20members%20could%20hold%20the%20key%20to%20the%20government%20formation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaba%20said%20that%20the%20structural%20changes%20that%20have%20taken%20place%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20might%20be%20difficult%20to%20undo%20once%20democracy%20and%20statehood%20is%20restored%3A%20%E2%80%9CThey%20may%20or%20may%20not%20work%20for%20the%20BJP%20but%20even%20if%20the%20party%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20come%20to%20power%2C%20some%20of%20the%20policies%20will%20have%20to%20continue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhatever%20is%20happening%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20is%20happening%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20Centre%20is%20behaving%20as%20per%20the%20political%20calculations%20of%20the%20BJP.%20Undoing%20of%20Article%20370%20had%20a%20political%20objective%20and%20these%20changes%20fall%20into%20that%20pattern.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702459854000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13140041%2F16147040338_e14a11ca31_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-will-the-supreme-courts-article-370-judgment-mean-for-politics-in-jk%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20to%20conduct%20assembly%20polls%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20by%20September%2030%2C%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-will-the-supreme-cour